  "prompt": "Which one is better C++ or Java?",
  "response": "The choice between C++ and Java depends on your specific needs and use case. Here's a comparison:\n\nC++ Advantages:\n- Faster performance\n- Direct memory management\n- Lower-level system programming\n- Used in game development, embedded systems\n- More control over hardware\n- Better for resource-intensive applications\n\nJava Advantages:\n- Platform independent (Write Once, Run Anywhere)\n- Automatic memory management\n- Easier to learn and use\n- Large standard library\n- Better for web and enterprise applications\n- Strong in mobile development (Android)\n- More robust security features\n\nChoose based on:\n1. Project requirements\n2. Performance needs\n3. Development speed\n4. Target platform\n5. Personal/team expertise\n\nNo universal \"better\" language - each has strengths in different domains.\n\nRecommendation:\n- Game/system programming: C++\n- Web/enterprise/mobile: Java\n- Learn both if possible, as skills are transferable",
